title: Second-quarter burst gives Parker a Homecoming win over Paxon
text:
Second-quarter burst gives Parker a Homecoming win over Paxon 
Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 12:26 am 
PARKER 40 
PAXON 3 
Star of the game: Erik Hill threw for 209 yards and Isaac Ricks ran for 135, leading Parker to a homecoming victory. 
Turning point: With the Braves (3-3) ahead 6-3 in the second quarter, Ricks scored on a 2-yard run and Hill on an 8-yard run to put some distance between Parker and the Golden Eagles (1-6). With time running out in the opening half, Paxon backup QB Ian Fennimore heaved a pass over the middle that was picked off by Aquana McCalop and taken back 67 yards for a TD as the half expired, putting Parker ahead 26-3. 
On defense: McCalop had two interceptions and Jai Williams added another for the Braves. ... The Parker defense held Paxon to 129 yards of offense. ... Paxon’s Gabe Devoe had two interceptions. 
Fast facts: Paxon RB Akari Boss rushed for 66 yards on eight carries. ... Hill was 9-of-19 passing and threw a 38-yard touchdown to Kelvin Bryant. Bryant finished with three catches for 76 yards. ... Malik Douglas caught two passes for 64 yards and Jonathan Brozovich caught three passes for 51 yards. ... It was Parker’s first win on homecoming since 2008. 
They said it: “We’re getting into the meat of our schedule and we are beginning to peak at the right time.” — Parker coach Tommy Balom George Wahl , The Times-Union
